pulltitle: Additional parameter (`attrs`) for create() and update() methods.
pullsbody:
There would be nice if we could pass some additional dictionary to these (`create()` and `update()`).
Now if we won't to add some value we need to override whole method.

With this little change we can do this: [[gist.github.com/863191]]
pull_commit_message: BaseHander: create() and update() now gets additional `attrs` parameter.

pullsbody:
You can see the issue : https://bitbucket.org/jespern/django-piston/issue/76/posting-xml-doesn-t-work 
I took the Patch from Tom Coote which is under GPL, and applied it to the git repository with a few tweakings.

However any review would be greatly appreciated :)

Regards, 

Olivier.
